## Security and Idempotency Audit Notes

- `src/engine/executors/github_pr.rs`: PR identity/check/CI command invocations use `Command::new(program).args(args)` through `GithubPrCommandRunner` and build `gh` argv vectors for `pr view`, `pr checks`, REST check-runs, and Actions job/log collection. No CodeRabbit or LLM text is inserted into shell strings by this module.
- `src/engine/executors/github_feedback.rs`: CodeRabbit collection queries are argv-based through the GitHub command runner. Marker execution reads local `pr-feedback-marker-report.json` before actions, queries remote issue comments before actions, parses hidden marker comments, and derives completion keys from stable marker key, source head SHA, remediation output head, body hash, action, and run id. Marker comment creation writes deterministic body JSON to a file and invokes `gh api ... --input <file>` rather than interpolating body text into a shell command.
- `src/engine/executors/feedback_eval.rs`: the production feedback evaluator process uses `Command::new(program).args(args)` with structured request JSON written to stdin; raw LLM output is persisted through the artifact store as bounded JSON data and is not embedded in argv.
- `src/engine/executors/pr_remediation.rs`: remediation wrapper, post-PR test runner, and push runner use argv request structs and `Command::new(&request.argv[0]).args(...)`; stdin is null. Structured artifacts are written via `PrFollowupArtifactStore`.
- `src/engine/executors/pr_followup_artifacts.rs` and `src/engine/executors/pr_followup_types.rs`: artifact paths are rooted under the configured artifact root with current/history namespaces; writes are atomic; store reads validate binding fields, family, sequence, and metadata. Shared binding/types derive serde serialization/deserialization and equality.
- Already-existing executor tests confirm idempotency and shell safety for GitHub PR argv, CodeRabbit API argv, feedback evaluator stdin/artifacts, remediation wrapper argv, marker comment body files/API input, and post-PR test/push argv. `cargo test --test github_pr_followup_executor_tests -- idempotency` and `-- shell_safety` passed.
- P19 did not add required behavior and did not add P19-owned expected-failing manifest entries. The expected-failing manifest remains empty and validates successfully.

